{"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/preserving-the-results-of-a-throwing-expression","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/swift-standard-library","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/numbers-and-basic-values","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sometimes you need to preserve the entire result of a function call or other expression"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that can either throw or return a value. For example, you may need to serialize the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"result or pass it as a value to another part of your app that handles the result"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"data. Use the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type in these scenarios to capture the result of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"potentially failing operation."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Identify a Throwing Expression to Preserve","anchor":"Identify-a-Throwing-Expression-to-Preserve"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Typically, you use "},{"code":"do-catch","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" statements to handle throwing expressions immediately,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but sometimes you need to store the whole result of the operation for later processing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"during tasks like analyzing a batch of calls. The following example introduces an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API that generates random numbers, but that fails approximately half of the time."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["enum EntropyError: Error {","    case entropyDepleted","}","","struct UnreliableRandomGenerator {","    func random() throws -> Int {","        if Bool.random() {","            return Int.random(in: 1...100)","        } else {","            throw EntropyError.entropyDepleted","        }","    }","}"]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Convert the Throwing Expression to a Result","anchor":"Convert-the-Throwing-Expression-to-a-Result"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You preserve the return value or thrown error from a throwing expression using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" enumeration’s "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/init(catching:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" initializer. Invoke"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the throwing expression inside the closure you pass to the initializer:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let singleSample = Result { try UnreliableRandomGenerator().random() }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In most scenarios, you use the preserved result as part of broader functionality"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in your code. For example, you may run a series of randomness tests and compute the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"statistical average of both a range of numbers returned from a random number generator,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as well as the failure rate of calling the API. In these cases, you need to store"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the whole result rather than just the success value or that the API call failed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example uses the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/init(catching:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" initializer in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"broader context of saving a series of calls for later statistical analysis:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct RandomnessMonitor {","    let randomnessSource: UnreliableRandomGenerator","    var results: [Result<Int, Error>] = []","","    init(generator: UnreliableRandomGenerator) {","        randomnessSource = generator","    }","","    mutating func sample() {","        let sample = Result { try randomnessSource.random() }","        results.append(sample)","    }","","    func summary() -> (Double, Double) {","        let totals = results.reduce((sum: 0, count: 0)) { total, sample in","            switch sample {","            case .success(let number):","                return (total.sum + number, total.count)","            case .failure:","                return (total.sum, total.count + 1)","            }","        }","","        return (","            average: Double(totals.sum) \/ Double(results.count - totals.count),","            failureRate: Double(totals.count) \/ Double(results.count)","        )","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Running the analysis on a sufficiently large sample generates an average number near"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"50 and a failure rate near 50%:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["var monitor = RandomnessMonitor(generator: UnreliableRandomGenerator())","(0..<1000).forEach { _ in monitor.sample() }","let (average, failureRate) = monitor.summary()","print(\"Average value: \\(average), failure rate: \\(failureRate * 100.0)%.\")","\/\/ Prints values such as: \"Average value: 47.95, failure rate: 48.69%.\""]}],"kind":"content"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Converting a Throwing Expression to a Result","anchor":"Converting-a-Throwing-Expression-to-a-Result","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/init(catching:)"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Call the initializer that wraps a throwing expression when you need to serialize"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or memoize the result."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Preserving the Results of a Throwing Expression"},"kind":"article","references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swift","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","type":"topic","title":"Swift","images":[{"identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","type":"card"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/swift-standard-library":{"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/swift-standard-library","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/swift-standard-library","type":"topic","title":"Swift Standard Library","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Solve complex problems and write high-performance, readable code.","type":"text"}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Result/init(catching:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/result\/init(catching:)","abstract":[{"text":"Creates a new result by evaluating a throwing closure, capturing the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"returned value as a success, or any thrown error as a failure."}],"title":"init(catching:)","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/init(catching:)","conformance":{"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Failure"},{"text":" conforms to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Error"},{"text":".","t